      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"interconnectedness\" thing sounds nice but it feels way too intentional to be just nature. The rhythm changes when the crowds are heaviest or when people seem particularly agitated. It's not just a random \"vibe,\" it's more like it's shifting to compensate for something. Have you ever looked into how low-frequency signals or modulated electrical hums can actually affect human neurological states? It feels less like \"harmony\" and more like synchronization.",
